From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 12 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: disable markdown README generation

In the Flatpak build environment the host markdown binary is visible at
/run/host/usr/bin/markdown but requires libmarkdown.so.3 which is not
present inside the Flatpak sandbox. cmake finds the binary via
find_program(), generates ALL targets for each README*.html, and the
build then fails at runtime with:

  markdown: error while loading shared libraries: libmarkdown.so.3

Force MARKDOWN to empty so the if(MARKDOWN) guard skips HTML generation
entirely. The source .md files are still installed as fallback.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -1126,1 +1126,1 @@
-find_program(MARKDOWN NAMES markdown kramdown pandoc)
+set(MARKDOWN "" CACHE FILEPATH "markdown converter" FORCE)
